For the following gas phase equilibrium reaction at constant temperature,
$$\text{NH}_3\text{(g)} \rightleftharpoons 1 / 2 \text{ N}_2\text{(g)} + 3 / 2 \text{H}_2\text{(g)}$$
if the total pressure is $\sqrt{3}\text{ atm}$ and the pressure equilibrium constant $(K_p)$ is $9\text{ atm}$, then the degree of dissociation is given as $(x \times 10^{-2})^{-1 / 2}$. The value of $x$ is $\dots\dots$. (nearest integer)
